docs.snippet: MONTEVIDEO, Feb. 21. -- President Gabriel Terra has called elections for April 8 to approve the new Uruguayan Constitution and to choose a new national administration. The opposition parties have announced they will not ballot, arguing that the...
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Feb. 21. -- President Gabriel Terra has called elections for April 8 to approve the new Uruguayan Constitution and to choose a new national administration. The opposition parties have announced they will not ballot, arguing that the Constituent Assembly was hand-picked by President Terra and does not represent public opinion.

headline.main: URUGUAYAN ELECTION SET.; Vote on New Constitution and for President to Be Cast April 8.

byline.original: Special Cable to THE NEW YORK TIMES

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 25. -- Despite the determined efforts of the League of Nations Chaco commission to maintain the strictest secrecy regarding its peace proposal to Bolivia and Paraguay, it is learned in Latin-American diplomatic circles here that...
docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 25. -- Despite the determined efforts of the League of Nations Chaco commission to maintain the strictest secrecy regarding its peace proposal to Bolivia and Paraguay, it is learned in Latin-American diplomatic circles here that the proposal is in the form of a draft of a definite peace treaty.
docs.abstract: Asked to urge Bolivia and Paraguay to accept League of Nations com peace proposal
